        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. (a) Selenops banksi, palp, ventral and retrolateral, highlighting various structures present in species belonging to the banksi group; dark pink – dRTA, teal – vRTA, yellow – MA, purple – C, pink – E, orange – EB, green – EA. (b) S. banksi, holotype male, palp, ventral and retrolateral (MCZ 20436) (c) S. banksi, ex-S. kikay syn. nov., palp, ventral, from Manaus, Brazil; image has been flipped horizontally (MCN 25526) (d) S. banksi, ex-S. kikay syn. nov., holotype male, from Itabuna, Brazil (MNRJ – destroyed) (e) S. micropalpus, holotype male, palp, ventral and retrolateral (AMNH) (f) S. ducke, holotype male, palp, ventral, image has been flipped horizontally (MCN 25527) (g) S. ducke, holotype male,palp, ventral, image has been flipped horizontally (MCN 25527) (h) S. ducke, holotype male, palp, retrolateral (MCN 25527)." ;
